title: -A Neutron Elastic Scattering Study of Cr,Fe and Ni In The Energy Region 1.77 To 2.76 Mev.-

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Nuclear Data for Reactors Conf., Helsinki 1970, Vol.2, p.327 (1970)

x4freetext: -A NEUTRON ELASTIC SCATTERING STUDY OF CR,FE AND NI
IN THE ENERGY REGION 1.77 TO 2.76 MEV.-
STUDSVIK 6 MEV VAN DE GRAAFF WITH A PULSED
.BEAM PULSE WIDTH AT HALF MAXIMUM  2 NANOSEC.,
CYLINDER HAVING LENGTH OF 5.0 CM, 0.95 CM
INNER DIAMETER AND 2.5 CM OUTER DIAMETER FOR CR,FE,NI.
.POLYTHENE SCATTERER,3.0 CM IN LENGTH,0.95 CM OUTER
.SCATTERING SAMPLES ARE POSITIONED WITH THEIR SYMMETRY
AXES PERPENDICULAR TO THAT OF THE TARGET
.SCINTILLATOR NE102A, 10 CM DIAMETER AND 5 CM LENGTH
.THE NEUTRON FLUX WAS MONITORED WITH A DIRECTIONAL
.THE DIFFERENT PIECES OF THE EFFICIENCY CURVE ARE
THE TOTAL N-P CROSS SECTIONS AT THE DIFFERENT NEUTRON
ENERGIES ARE CITED FROM  A.HORSLEY, NUCL. DATA.
.THE SIGNAL-TO-BACKGROUND RATIO AT THE POSITION OF THE
HAUSER-FESHBACH THEORY WITH AND WITHOUT CORRECTION FOR
WIDTH-FLUCTUATION AGREE WITH THE EXPERIMENTAL DATA
.THE EXPERIMENTAL DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR ATTENUATION,
ANISOTROPY OF THE NEUTRON FLUX IN THE SCATTERER,
MULTIPLE ELASTIC SCATTERING, AND FOR THE FINITE
GEOMETRIES BY A MONTE CARLO PROGRAM. THE PROGRAM BY
.STATISTICAL ERRORS FOR THE NUMBER OF COUNTS IN THE
ELASTIC PEAKS OF THE TOF SPECTRA LESS THAN 2 PERCENT,
.STATISTICAL ERROR FOR THE NUMBER OF MONITOR COUNTS
.THE EXPERIMENTAL CROSS SECTION ERRORS ARE 10 PERCENT,
